org.universAAL.middleware.interfaces.configuration.configurationDefinitionTypes

Interface DescribedEntity

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ConfigurableEntityEditor, ConfigurationFile, ConfigurationFileEditor, ConfigurationParameter, ConfigurationParameterEditor
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConfigurationDefinedElsewhere, GenericConfigurationEntity, LocalConfigurationEntity, LocalConfigurationFileEditor, LocalConfigurationParameterEditor, RemoteConfigurationEntity, RemoteConfigurationFileEditor, RemoteConfigurationParamaterEditor

    public interface DescribedEntity
    A DescribedEntity is an Entity that is restricted to certain Scope and has a description.
    Author:
    amedrano

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      String getDescription(Locale loc)
      Description of the entity.
      Scope getScope()
      Define the ID and Scope for this Entity.

    • Method Detail

      • getScope

        Scope getScope()
        Define the ID and Scope for this Entity.
        • SpaceScope defines that this entity is applicable over the whole Space, so when managed its value will be the same on the whole Space.
        • InstanceScope defines that this entity is only applicable for the instance given in the scope.
        • ModuleScope the entity is only applicable for the given module and instance.
        • ApplicationScope defines that this entity is applicable over a certain application, this will be shared over the whole Space for the same application.
        • AppPartScope same as ApplicationScope but with finer grain, for application parts.
        Returns:
        a valid scope.

      • getDescription

        String getDescription(Locale loc)
        Description of the entity. It can be localized so the description can be given in different languages.
        Parameters:
        loc - the preferred locale for the description.
        Returns:
        the Description of the entity.
